  "body": "This might be an ether-pudding issue. Has something changed about the way contract functions are promisified? \n\nUsing test-rpc:\n\n```\nvar promise = myContract.myMethod({ from: account[0] });\nconsole.log('promise =' + JSON.stringify(promise)); \n\n// Output for Truffle 1.0.3\n// $ promise = {\"isFulfilled\":false,\"isRejected\":false}\n\n// Output for Truffle 2.0.1\n// $ promise = {}\n```\n\nTests using chai-as-promised hang or break on 2.0.1. Just curious . . . Thanks so much for migrations! Awesome!    \n",
