    "body": "Confirmed: its a weird chai-as-promised/native promises thing. The problem is actually with 'should' pattern tests. Tests that use expect (and probably assert) work fine in v2.\n\nIn v1 with a bluebird promise you can have a contract method like:\n\n```\nfunction throwsError(){\n    throw;\n}\n```\n\nand write tests with chai-as-promised like:\n\n```\nit('should throw an error', function(){\n     return myContract.throwsError({from: account[0]}).should.eventually.be.rejected;\n}\n```\n\nIn v2 these fail (possibly because the returned promise object is empty). Wrapping the method call in a chai 'expect' function works though:\n\n```\nit('should throw an error', function(){\n    return  expect(myContract.throwsError({from: account[0]})).to.eventually.be.rejected;\n}\n```\n\nClosing, thanks.  \n",
